fields.description:
Currently, to have the latest commit in the main branch you have to make 2 requests.

This can be improved for the REST API users if the main-branch would be part of the metadata of a repository.

This would also make the API symmetric with the "PUT repository updates":\\
{{PUT https://api.bitbucket.org/1.0/repositories/{accountname}/{repo_slug}}}

The following becomes obsolete:\\
{{GET https://api.bitbucket.org/1.0/repositories/{accountname}/{repo_slug}/main-branch}}

And the following returns also {{main_branch}} in the metadata:\\
{{GET https://api.bitbucket.org/1.0/repositories/{accountname}/{repo_slug}}}

For example, i have description:

{code}
#!

Merged in adyachenko/nazya/issue-geoip ([PR#1566|https://bitbucket.org/site/master/pull-requests/1566])

Фиксит нечто
{code}

When an annotated tag is created like this:

{code}
git tag -a v0.1 -m "An annotated tag"
git push origin v0.1
{code}

The tag message cannot be viewed in Bitbucket web page. Only way to view the tag is to clone the repository and use the command:

{code}
git show v0.1
{code}
